|doi=10.1016/S1474-4422(05)70071-5
|url=
}}</ref> However only between 30 and 70% of persons with CIS would later develop MS.<ref name="pmid15847841"/> The disease usually presents with sensorial (46% of cases), visual (33%), cerebellar(30%) and motor (26%) symptoms.<ref name="pmid17952303">{{cite journal
