Multiple sclerosis relapses are often unpredictable and can occur without warning with no obvious inciting factors. Some attacks, however, are preceded by common triggers. Relapses occur more frequently during spring and summer.<ref name="pmid16804331">{{cite journal
|author=Tataru N, Vidal C, Decavel P, Berger E, Rumbach L
